Windows RDS Access:
-	Create an Ec2 instance ( Key Pair -> opt for .pem)
-	Once the instance is running -> Actions -> Security -> Get Windows Password
-	Upload Windows Key File
-	Select the .pem that we created earlier
-	Decrypt password and copy it
-	Copy the public ip
-	On local Machine search for Remote Desktop Connection
-	In RDP, Paste the public Ip we copied earlier -> Connect
-	Administrator and the decrypted password as credentials 

Linux Putty Access
-	Create an Ec2 instance ( Key Pair -> opt for .ppk)
-	Copy Public ip
-	Open Putty -> Paste the public ip
-	SSH -> Auth -> credentials -> Public -> Key Authentication -> browse
